race.comment: The promising CALL ME BASIL (1) has won two of his last three, clocking in at least four lengths ahead on each occasion. Stepped up to 1500m for the first time at Port Macquarie last start and led all the way for an effortless win. Good enough to go to this next level. ALABAMA BLITZ (2) led for home but dropped off soon after when resuming over 1350m at the Beaumont track last time out. Scored comfortably over the mile at Newcastle when second-up last prep. Capable of sharp improvement. ROSE'S LEGACY (9) was eased out of the race last time at Kembla. Should improve today at the third run back. SIR TUA (11) was too good at Nowra last start when out to the mile for the first time. Can go on with the job.
